title: Independent Candidate Zahid Ullah Khan wins PK-99 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate Zahid Ullah Khan won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-99, Bannu-I by securing 27,792 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Sher Azam Khan who bagged 27,253 votes.
Overall voters turnout remained 37.18 percent.
